group).
DISCUSSION: Orthognathic treatment seems to provide good outcomes at relatively 
low cost. Even allowing for the uncertainty in mean costs and QALYs, there is a 
high probability of treatment being cost-effective. Cost-utility analysis is 
still a relatively new technique in dentistry and further studies should be 
encouraged.

