specific domain for vitality and a utility instrument.
RESULTS: The study group with nocturia had a significantly lower level of 
vitality and utility, and greater impairment of work and activity, than the 
control group. Women were more affected than men. Symptom severity correlated 
with all three measures.
CONCLUSIONS: In an otherwise healthy and professionally active group of 
individuals, waking at night to void significantly diminishes their overall 
well-being, vitality and productivity, leading to a significant level of 
indirect and intangible costs.

