Does overexpression of Cu,Zn-SOD extend life span in Drosophila melanogaster?

Orr WC(1), Sohal RS.

Author information:
(1)Department of Biological Sciences, Southern Methodist University, Dallas, TX 
75275, USA. borr@mail.smu.edu

The argument is presented here that, while there exists considerable correlative 
evidence supporting the oxidative stress hypothesis of aging, key experiments to 
test this hypothesis using Drosophila transgenics overexpressing Cu,Zn-SOD fall 
short in providing validation. In particular, significant life span extensions 
tend to be observed when the backgrounds of the control flies are relatively 
short-lived, suggesting that bolstering antioxidative defenses is only effective 
in compromised genetic backgrounds. Other shortcomings of the transgenic 
approaches adopted to date will be summarized.

